CSS styling of html:
Syntax:
selectior {property1: value1, property2: value2. ....}
h1 {
    font-size: 42px;
    color: purple;
}
to add the css file in the html we use:
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="#">
href - we specify the path to the css file.
selectors:

// to select a class="smth" -->
.smth { property1: value1 ..... }

// to select by id="new" -->
#new { prop1: val1 .... }

*** can be combined
//combine class + item
a.login {prop1: val1} ... will select the <a> tags with the class='login'

// id + children (selects onlu the immediate children)
-- #news > h1 - will select the h1s that are directly in the item with id='news'
!!! note that if we have a div or and article with h1 in it also in the #news -->
this inner div will NOT be selected. We have to specify it with his parent
 -- #news article > h1
 -- #news artticle p - will select all 'p's in the article tag
 -- #news p > b.red - will select the 'b' tags in the 'p' child with class name=red
 -- #news span.date - will select the span tag with class=date

 // multiple selections
 article>p, section>p - will select both 'p's from the article and section

